British nationals donâ€™t need a visa to enter Gibraltar.
For further information on entry requirements, check the website of HM Government of Gibraltar.
Passport validity
You must hold a valid passport to enter Gibraltar. Your passport must be valid for the proposed duration of your stay. No additional period of validity beyond this is required.
If you plan to travel to or from Gibraltar to Spain, you should be aware that entry requirements for Spain may change after the UK leaves the EU. If the UK leaves with a deal, travel to the EU will remain the same as now until at least 31 December 2020. If the UK leaves the EU without a deal, the rules for travelling or working in Europe will change. See travel advice Spain for more information.
UK Emergency Travel Documents
UK Emergency Travel Documents are accepted for entry, airside transit and exit from Gibraltar.
